msContents.summary: A service book, according to the Yemenite rite.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 17 19; written lines: 17 19; Uniform layout. Visible mastara ruling. Catchword on every page. Running title.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 18th to 19th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Yemenite Service-Book. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 6354.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Raffalovich and Lifkin: purchased by the British Museum from them on 15 April 1902: inscribed, folio [227v].
